What makes an account "inauthentic"? 

We're considering a new labelling system for inauthentic accounts. These accounts, often incorrectly called bots, will be hidden from like counts and other metrics in Warpcast. 

Inauthentic accounts give real people the ick because they're clearly trying to get value for their account at the expense of everyone else on the network.

cast.text:
Before the conclave, Bocconi ran a ‚ÄúNetwork Conclave‚Äù sim.  
Graph theory only ‚Äî no AI, no divine signals.

They surfaced Robert Prevost as a top node.  
Days later: Pope Leo XIV.

Eigenvector = status  
Betweenness = info flow  
Coalitions = emergent power

The Vatican didn‚Äôt run this.  
The network did.

Leadership emerges from structure, not hierarchy.  
Forget hierarchy. Observe the graph.

Link: https://www.unibocconi.it/en/news/network-conclave  
(now you see why @balajis.eth was right)
